            <h2>About Him</h2>
            <p>
                Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam (1931–2015) was an Indian aerospace scientist 
                and the 11th President of India. He played a crucial role in the 
                development of India's missile and nuclear programs, earning him the 
                title “Missile Man of India.” His dedication, simplicity, and love 
                for students made him one of the most respected figures in modern India.
            </p>

            <h2>Achievements</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Developed India’s first Satellite Launch Vehicle (SLV-III)</li>
                <li>Key role in Pokhran-II nuclear tests</li>
                <li>President of India (2002–2007)</li>
                <li>Bharat Ratna Award recipient</li>
                <li>Author of inspirational books like *Wings of Fire*</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Inspiration</h2>
            <p>
                Dr. Kalam believed in dreaming big and working hard to achieve it.
                His life continues to inspire millions around the world.
            </p>
        </section>

